  "prompt": "Can I deactivate my Roku device?",
  "response": "Yes, you can deactivate your Roku device if you want to unlink it from your Roku account or prepare it for resale or disposal. Here\u2019s how to deactivate your Roku device:\n\n---\n\n### **1. Remove the Device from Your Roku Account**\nTo unlink your Roku device from your Roku account:\n1. Go to the [Roku website](https://my.roku.com/) and log in to your account.\n2. Navigate to **My Account** > **Manage Your Devices**.\n3. Find the Roku device you want to deactivate and click **Deactivate**.\n4. Confirm the deactivation.\n\n---\n\n### **2. Factory Reset the Device (Optional)**\nIf you\u2019re planning to sell or give away the device, perform a factory reset to remove all personal data:\n1. On your Roku device, go to **Settings** > **System** > **Advanced System Settings** > **Factory Reset**.\n2. Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the reset.\n\n---\n\n### **3. Unlink from the Roku Mobile App (Optional)**\nIf you\u2019ve used the Roku mobile app, make sure to remove the device from the app:\n1. Open the Roku mobile app on your smartphone or tablet.\n2. Navigate to the **Devices** section and remove the deactivated Roku device.\n\n---\n\nBy following these steps, your Roku device will be fully deactivated and ready for use by someone else or safely stored away.",
